aiobungie.api

API interfaces that're used for standard aiobungie client implementations.

They expose the methods along with its documentations. Which also can be used as type-hints.

23"""API interfaces that're used for standard aiobungie client implementations.
24
25They expose the methods along with its documentations. Which also can be used as type-hints.
26"""
27
28from __future__ import annotations
29
30__all__: tuple[str, ...] = ("RESTClient", "Framework")
31
32from .framework import Framework
33from .rest import RESTClient
class RESTClient(aiobungie.traits.RESTful, abc.ABC): 
  69class RESTClient(traits.RESTful, abc.ABC):
  70    """An API interface for functionality that a REST API implementation provides."""
  71
  72    __slots__ = ()
  73
  74    if typing.TYPE_CHECKING:
  75
  76        async def __aenter__(self) -> Self: ...
  77
  78        async def __aexit__(
  79            self,
  80            exception_type: type[BaseException] | None,
  81            exception: BaseException | None,
  82            exception_traceback: types.TracebackType | None,
  83        ) -> None: ...
  84
  85    @abc.abstractmethod
  86    async def read_manifest_bytes(self, language: _ALLOWED_LANGS = "en", /) -> bytes:
  87        """Read raw manifest SQLite database bytes response.
  88
  89        This method can be used to write the bytes to zipped file
  90        and then extract it to get the manifest content.
  91
  92        Parameters
  93        ----------
  94        language : `str`
  95            The manifest database language bytes to get.
  96
  97        Returns
  98        -------
  99        `bytes`
 100            The bytes to read and write the manifest database.
 101        """
 102
 103    @abc.abstractmethod
 104    async def fetch_manifest_path(self) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 105        """Fetch the manifest JSON paths.
 106
 107        Returns
 108        -------
 109        `typedefs.JSONObject`
 110            The manifest JSON paths.
 111        """
 112
 113    @abc.abstractmethod
 114    async def download_json_manifest(
 115        self,
 116        file_name: str = "manifest",
 117        path: str | pathlib.Path = ".",
 118        *,
 119        language: _ALLOWED_LANGS = "en",
 120        executor: concurrent.futures.Executor | None = None,
 121    ) -> pathlib.Path:
 122        """Download the Bungie manifest json file.
 123
 124        Example
 125        -------
 126        ```py
 127        manifest = await rest.download_json_manifest()
 128        with open(manifest, "r") as f:
 129            to_dict = json.loads(f.read())
 130            item_definitions = to_dict['DestinyInventoryItemDefinition']
 131        ```
 132
 133        Parameters
 134        ----------
 135        file_name: `str`
 136            The file name to save the manifest json file. Default is `manifest`.
 137        path: `str` | `pathlib.Path`
 138            The path to save the manifest json file. Default is the current directory. Example `"D:/"`
 139        language: `str`
 140            The manifest database language bytes to get. Default is English.
 141        executor: `concurrent.futures.Executor | None`
 142            An optional executor which will be used to write the bytes of the manifest.
 143
 144        Returns
 145        -------
 146        `pathlib.Path`
 147            The path of this JSON manifest.
 148        """
 149
 150    @abc.abstractmethod
 151    async def download_sqlite_manifest(
 152        self,
 153        language: _ALLOWED_LANGS = "en",
 154        name: str = "manifest",
 155        path: str | pathlib.Path = ".",
 156        *,
 157        force: bool = False,
 158        executor: concurrent.futures.Executor | None = None,
 159    ) -> pathlib.Path:
 160        """Downloads the SQLite version of Destiny2's Manifest.
 161
 162        Example
 163        -------
 164        ```py
 165        manifest = await rest.download_sqlite_manifest()
 166        with sqlite3.connect(manifest) as conn:
 167            ...
 168        ```
 169
 170        Parameters
 171        ----------
 172        language : `str`
 173            The manifest language to download, Default is English.
 174        path: `str` | `pathlib.Path`
 175            The path to download this manifest. Example `"/tmp/databases/"`, Default is the current directory.
 176        name : `str`
 177            The manifest database file name. Default is `manifest`
 178        force : `bool`
 179            Whether to force the download. Default is `False`. However if set to true the old
 180            file will get unlinked and a new one will begin to download.
 181        executor: `concurrent.futures.Executor | None`
 182            An optional executor which will be used to write the bytes of the manifest.
 183
 184        Returns
 185        --------
 186        `pathlib.Path`
 187            A pathlib object of the `.sqlite` file.
 188
 189        Raises
 190        ------
 191        `FileExistsError`
 192            If the manifest file exists and `force` is `False`.
 193        `ValueError`
 194            If the provided language was not recognized.
 195        """
 196

 200
 201        Returns

 204            The manifest version.

 207    @abc.abstractmethod
 208    async def fetch_bungie_user(self, id: int) -> typedefs.JSONObject:

 211        Parameters
 212        ----------

 215
 216        Returns

 218        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 219            A JSON object of users objects.
 220
 221        Raises
 222        ------
 223        `aiobungie.error.NotFound`
 224            The user was not found.
 225        """

 232        ----------
 233        name : `str`
 234            The user name.
 235
 236        Returns
 237        -------

 239            A JSON object of an array of the found users.
 240
 241        Raises
 242        ------
 243        `aiobungie.NotFound`
 244            The user(s) was not found.
 245
 246        """

 275    @abc.abstractmethod
 276    async def fetch_hardlinked_credentials(
 277        self,
 278        credential: int,
 279        type: enums.CredentialType | int = enums.CredentialType.STEAMID,
 280        /,
 281    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 282        """Gets any hard linked membership given a credential.
 283
 284        Only works for credentials that are public just `aiobungie.CredentialType.STEAMID` right now.
 285        Cross Save aware.
 286
 287        Parameters
 288        ----------
 289        credential: `int`
 290            A valid SteamID64
 291        type: `aiobungie.aiobungie.CredentialType | int`
 292            The credential type. This must not be changed
 293            Since its only credential that works "currently"
 294
 295        Returns
 296        -------
 297        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 298            A JSON object of the found user hard linked types.
 299        """

 307    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:

 328    @abc.abstractmethod
 329    async def fetch_profile(
 330        self,
 331        membership_id: int,
 332        type: enums.MembershipType | int,
 333        components: collections.Sequence[enums.ComponentType],
 334        auth: str | None = None,
 335    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 336        """
 337        Fetch a bungie profile.
 338
 339        Parameters
 340        ----------
 341        membership_id: `int`
 342            The member's id.
 343        type: `aiobungie.aiobungie.MembershipType | int`
 344            A valid membership type.
 345        components : `collections.Sequence[aiobungie.ComponentType]`
 346            A sequence of profile components to collect and return.
 347
 348        Other Parameters
 349        ----------------
 350        auth : `str | None`
 351            A bearer access_token to make the request with.
 352            This is optional and limited to components that only requires an Authorization token.
 353
 354        Returns
 355        --------
 356        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 357            A JSON object of the found profile.
 358
 359        Raises
 360        ------
 361        `aiobungie.MembershipTypeError`
 362            The provided membership type was invalid.
 363        """
 364
 365    @abc.abstractmethod
 366    async def fetch_membership(
 367        self,
 368        name: str,
 369        code: int,
 370        type: enums.MembershipType | int = enums.MembershipType.ALL,
 371        /,
 372    ) -> typedefs.JSONArray:
 373        """Fetch a Destiny 2 Player.
 374
 375        Parameters
 376        -----------
 377        name: `str`
 378            The unique Bungie player name.
 379        code : `int`
 380            The unique Bungie display name code.
 381        type: `aiobungie.aiobungie.MembershipType | int`
 382            The player's membership type, e,g. XBOX, STEAM, PSN
 383
 384        Returns
 385        --------
 386        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONArray`
 387            A JSON array of the found player's memberships.
 388
 389        Raises
 390        ------
 391        `aiobungie.NotFound`
 392            The player was not found.
 393        `aiobungie.MembershipTypeError`
 394            The provided membership type was invalid.
 395        """

 397    @abc.abstractmethod
 398    async def fetch_character(
 399        self,
 400        member_id: int,
 401        membership_type: enums.MembershipType | int,
 402        character_id: int,
 403        components: collections.Sequence[enums.ComponentType],
 404        auth: str | None = None,
 405    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 406        """Fetch a Destiny 2 player's characters.
 407
 408        Parameters
 409        ----------
 410        member_id: `int`
 411            A valid bungie member id.
 412        membership_type: `aiobungie.aiobungie.internal.enums.MembershipType | int`
 413            The member's membership type.
 414        character_id : `int`
 415            The character id to return.
 416        components: `collections.Sequence[aiobungie.ComponentType]`
 417            A list of character components to collect and return.
 418
 419        Other Parameters
 420        ----------------
 421        auth : `str | None`
 422            A bearer access_token to make the request with.
 423            This is optional and limited to components that only requires an Authorization token.
 424
 425        Returns
 426        -------
 427        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 428            A JSON object of the requested character.
 429
 430        Raises
 431        ------
 432        `aiobungie.MembershipTypeError`
 433            The provided membership type was invalid.
 434        """

 436    @abc.abstractmethod
 437    async def fetch_activities(
 438        self,
 439        member_id: int,
 440        character_id: int,
 441        mode: enums.GameMode | int,
 442        membership_type: enums.MembershipType | int = enums.MembershipType.ALL,
 443        *,
 444        page: int = 1,
 445        limit: int = 1,
 446    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 447        """Fetch a Destiny 2 activity for the specified user id and character.
 448
 449        Parameters
 450        ----------
 451        member_id: `int`
 452            The user id that starts with `4611`.
 453        character_id: `int`
 454            The id of the character to retrieve.
 455        mode: `aiobungie.aiobungie.GameMode | int`
 456            This parameter filters the game mode, Nightfall, Strike, Iron Banner, etc.
 457
 458        Other Parameters
 459        ----------------
 460        membership_type: `aiobungie.aiobungie.internal.enums.MembershipType | int`
 461            The Member ship type, if nothing was passed than it will return all.
 462        page: `int`
 463            The page number. Default to `1`
 464        limit: `int`
 465            Limit the returned result. Default to `1`
 466
 467        Returns
 468        -------
 469        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 470            A JSON object of the player's activities.
 471
 472        Raises
 473        ------
 474        `aiobungie.error.NotFound`
 475            The activity was not found.
 476
 477        `aiobungie.MembershipTypeError`
 478            The provided membership type was invalid.
 479        """
 480

 496    @abc.abstractmethod
 497    async def report_player(
 498        self,
 499        access_token: str,
 500        /,
 501        activity_id: int,
 502        character_id: int,
 503        reason_hashes: collections.Sequence[int],
 504        reason_category_hashes: collections.Sequence[int],
 505    ) -> None:
 506        """Report a player that you met in an activity that was engaging in ToS-violating activities.
 507
 508        .. note::
 509            This method requires `BnetWrite` OAuth2 scope.
 510
 511        Both you and the offending player must have played in the `activity_id` passed in.
 512        Please use this judiciously and only when you have strong suspicions of violation, pretty please.
 513
 514        Parameters
 515        ----------
 516        access_token: `str`
 517            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account that
 518            will be used to make the request with.
 519        activity_id: `int`
 520            The activity where you ran into the person you're reporting.
 521        character_id: `int`
 522            The character ID of the person you're reporting.
 523        reason_hashes: `Sequence[int]`
 524            [See](https://bungie-net.github.io/multi/schema_Destiny-Reporting-Requests-DestinyReportOffensePgcrRequest.html#schema_Destiny-Reporting-Requests-DestinyReportOffensePgcrRequest)
 525        reason_category_hashes: `Sequence[int]`
 526            [See](https://bungie-net.github.io/multi/schema_Destiny-Reporting-Requests-DestinyReportOffensePgcrRequest.html#schema_Destiny-Reporting-Requests-DestinyReportOffensePgcrRequest)
 527        """
 528
 529    @abc.abstractmethod
 530    async def fetch_clan_from_id(
 531        self, id: int, /, access_token: str | None = None
 532    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 533        """Fetch a Bungie Clan by its id.
 534
 535        Parameters
 536        -----------
 537        id : `int`
 538            The clan id.
 539
 540        Other Parameters
 541        ----------------
 542        access_token : `str | None`
 543            An optional access token to make the request with.
 544
 545            If the token was bound to a member of the clan,
 546            This field `aiobungie.crates.Clan.current_user_membership` will be available
 547            and will return the membership of the user who made this request.
 548
 549        Returns
 550        --------
 551        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 552            A JSON object of the clan.
 553
 554        Raises
 555        ------
 556        `aiobungie.NotFound`
 557            The clan was not found.
 558        """
 559
 560    @abc.abstractmethod
 561    async def fetch_clan(
 562        self,
 563        name: str,
 564        /,
 565        access_token: str | None = None,
 566        *,
 567        type: enums.GroupType | int = enums.GroupType.CLAN,
 568    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 569        """Fetch a Clan by its name.
 570        This method will return the first clan found with given name name.
 571
 572        Parameters
 573        ----------
 574        name : `str`
 575            The clan name.
 576
 577        Other Parameters
 578        ----------------
 579        access_token : `str | None`
 580            An optional access token to make the request with.
 581
 582            If the token was bound to a member of the clan,
 583            This field `aiobungie.crates.Clan.current_user_membership` will be available
 584            and will return the membership of the user who made this request.
 585        type : `aiobungie.aiobungie.GroupType | int`
 586            The group type, Default is one.
 587
 588        Returns
 589        -------
 590        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 591            A JSON object of the clan.
 592
 593        Raises
 594        ------
 595        `aiobungie.NotFound`
 596            The clan was not found.
 597        """

 634    @abc.abstractmethod
 635    async def search_group(
 636        self,
 637        name: str,
 638        group_type: enums.GroupType | int,
 639        *,
 640        creation_date: clans.GroupDate | int = 0,
 641        sort_by: int | None = None,
 642        group_member_count_filter: typing.Literal[0, 1, 2, 3] | None = None,
 643        locale_filter: str | None = None,
 644        tag_text: str | None = None,
 645        items_per_page: int | None = None,
 646        current_page: int | None = None,
 647        request_token: str | None = None,
 648    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 649        """Search for groups.
 650
 651        .. note::
 652            If the group type is set to `CLAN`, then parameters `group_member_count_filter`,
 653            `locale_filter` and `tag_text` must be `None`, otherwise `ValueError` will be raised.
 654
 655        Parameters
 656        ----------
 657        name : `str`
 658            The group name.
 659        group_type : `aiobungie.GroupType | int`
 660            The group type that's being searched for.
 661
 662        Other Parameters
 663        ----------------
 664        creation_date : `aiobungie.GroupDate | int`
 665            The creation date of the group. Defaults to `0` which is all time.
 666        sort_by : `int | None`
 667            ...
 668        group_member_count_filter : `int | None`
 669            ...
 670        locale_filter : `str | None`
 671            ...
 672        tag_text : `str | None`
 673            ...
 674        items_per_page : `int | None`
 675            ...
 676        current_page : `int | None`
 677            ...
 678        request_token : `str | None`
 679            ...
 680
 681        Returns
 682        --------
 683        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
 684            A JSON object of the search results.
 685
 686        Raises
 687        ------
 688        `ValueError`
 689            If the group type is `aiobungie.GroupType.CLAN` and `group_member_count_filter`,
 690            `locale_filter` and `tag_text` are not `None`.
 691        """

1102    @abc.abstractmethod
1103    async def edit_clan_options(
1104        self,
1105        access_token: str,
1106        /,
1107        group_id: int,
1108        *,
1109        invite_permissions_override: bool | None = None,
1110        update_culture_permissionOverride: bool | None = None,
1111        host_guided_game_permission_override: typing.Literal[0, 1, 2] | None = None,
1112        update_banner_permission_override: bool | None = None,
1113        join_level: enums.ClanMemberType | int | None = None,
1114    ) -> None:
1115        """Edit the clan options.
1116
1117        Notes
1118        -----
1119        * This request requires OAuth2: oauth2: `AdminGroups` scope.
1120        * All arguments will default to `None` if not provided. This does not include `access_token` and `group_id`
1121
1122        Parameters
1123        ----------
1124        access_token : `str`
1125            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
1126        group_id: `int`
1127            The group id.
1128
1129        Other Parameters
1130        ----------------
1131        invite_permissions_override : `bool | None`
1132            Minimum Member Level allowed to invite new members to group
1133            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder
1134            True means admins have this power, false means they don't
1135            Default is False for clans, True for groups.
1136        update_culture_permissionOverride : `bool | None`
1137            Minimum Member Level allowed to update group culture
1138            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder
1139            True means admins have this power, false means they don't
1140            Default is False for clans, True for groups.
1141        host_guided_game_permission_override : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]]`
1142            Minimum Member Level allowed to host guided games
1143            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder, Admin
1144            Allowed Overrides: `0` -> None, `1` -> Beginner `2` -> Member.
1145            Default is Member for clans, None for groups, although this means nothing for groups.
1146        update_banner_permission_override : `bool | None`
1147            Minimum Member Level allowed to update banner
1148            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder
1149            True means admins have this power, false means they don't
1150            Default is False for clans, True for groups.
1151        join_level : `aiobungie.ClanMemberType`
1152            Level to join a member at when accepting an invite, application, or joining an open clan.
1153            Default is `aiobungie.ClanMemberType.BEGINNER`
1154        """

1156    @abc.abstractmethod
1157    async def edit_clan(
1158        self,
1159        access_token: str,
1160        /,
1161        group_id: int,
1162        *,
1163        name: str | None = None,
1164        about: str | None = None,
1165        motto: str | None = None,
1166        theme: str | None = None,
1167        tags: collections.Sequence[str] | None = None,
1168        is_public: bool | None = None,
1169        locale: str | None = None,
1170        avatar_image_index: int | None = None,
1171        membership_option: enums.MembershipOption | int | None = None,
1172        allow_chat: bool | None = None,
1173        chat_security: typing.Literal[0, 1] | None = None,
1174        call_sign: str | None = None,
1175        homepage: typing.Literal[0, 1, 2] | None = None,
1176        enable_invite_messaging_for_admins: bool | None = None,
1177        default_publicity: typing.Literal[0, 1, 2] | None = None,
1178        is_public_topic_admin: bool | None = None,
1179    ) -> None:
1180        """Edit a clan.
1181
1182        Notes
1183        -----
1184        * This request requires OAuth2: oauth2: `AdminGroups` scope.
1185        * All arguments will default to `None` if not provided. This does not include `access_token` and `group_id`
1186
1187        Parameters
1188        ----------
1189        access_token : `str`
1190            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
1191        group_id: `int`
1192            The group id to edit.
1193
1194        Other Parameters
1195        ----------------
1196        name : `str | None`
1197            The name to edit the clan with.
1198        about : `str | None`
1199            The about section to edit the clan with.
1200        motto : `str | None`
1201            The motto section to edit the clan with.
1202        theme : `str | None`
1203            The theme name to edit the clan with.
1204        tags : `collections.Sequence[str] | None`
1205            A sequence of strings to replace the clan tags with.
1206        is_public : `bool | None`
1207            If provided and set to `True`, The clan will set to private.
1208            If provided and set to `False`, The clan will set to public whether it was or not.
1209        locale : `str | None`
1210            The locale section to edit the clan with.
1211        avatar_image_index : `int | None`
1212            The clan avatar image index to edit the clan with.
1213        membership_option : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[aiobungie.aiobungie.MembershipOption | int]` # noqa: E501 # Line too long
1214            The clan membership option to edit it with.
1215        allow_chat : `bool | None`
1216            If provided and set to `True`, The clan members will be allowed to chat.
1217            If provided and set to `False`, The clan members will not be allowed to chat.
1218        chat_security : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1]]`
1219            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat security will be edited to `Group` only.
1220            If provided and set to `1`, The clan chat security will be edited to `Admin` only.
1221        call_sign : `str | None`
1222            The clan call sign to edit it with.
1223        homepage : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]]`
1224            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat homepage will be edited to `Wall`.
1225            If provided and set to `1`, The clan chat homepage will be edited to `Forum`.
1226            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat homepage will be edited to `AllianceForum`.
1227        enable_invite_messaging_for_admins : `bool | None`
1228            ???
1229        default_publicity : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]]`
1230            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat publicity will be edited to `Public`.
1231            If provided and set to `1`, The clan chat publicity will be edited to `Alliance`.
1232            If provided and set to `2`, The clan chat publicity will be edited to `Private`.
1233        is_public_topic_admin : `bool | None`
1234            ???
1235        """

1411        security: typing.Literal[0, 1] = 0,
1412    ) -> None:
1413        """Add a new chat channel to a group.
1414
1415        .. note::
1416            This request requires OAuth2: AdminGroups scope.
1417

1421            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.

1426        ----------------
1427        name: `aiobungie.UndefinedOr[str]`
1428            The chat name. Default to `UNDEFINED`
1429        security: `typing.Literal[0, 1]`
1430            The security level of the chat.
1431

1560    @abc.abstractmethod
1561    async def fetch_fireteams(
1562        self,
1563        activity_type: fireteams.FireteamActivity | int,
1564        *,
1565        platform: fireteams.FireteamPlatform | int,
1566        language: fireteams.FireteamLanguage | str,
1567        date_range: fireteams.FireteamDate | int = 0,
1568        page: int = 0,
1569        slots_filter: int = 0,
1570    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
1571        """Fetch public Bungie fireteams with open slots.
1572
1573        Parameters
1574        ----------
1575        activity_type : `aiobungie.aiobungie.crates.FireteamActivity | int`
1576            The fireteam activity type.
1577
1578        Other Parameters
1579        ----------------
1580        platform : `aiobungie.aiobungie.crates.fireteams.FireteamPlatform | int`
1581            If this is provided. Then the results will be filtered with the given platform.
1582            Defaults to `aiobungie.crates.FireteamPlatform.ANY` which returns all platforms.
1583        language : `aiobungie.crates.fireteams.FireteamLanguage | str`
1584            A locale language to filter the used language in that fireteam.
1585            Defaults to `aiobungie.crates.FireteamLanguage.ALL`
1586        date_range : `aiobungie.aiobungie.FireteamDate | int`
1587            An integer to filter the date range of the returned fireteams. Defaults to `aiobungie.FireteamDate.ALL`.
1588        page : `int`
1589            The page number. By default its `0` which returns all available activities.
1590        slots_filter : `int`
1591            Filter the returned fireteams based on available slots. Default is `0`
1592
1593        Returns
1594        -------
1595        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
1596            A JSON object of the fireteam details.
1597        """

1807    @abc.abstractmethod
1808    async def insert_socket_plug(
1809        self,
1810        action_token: str,
1811        /,
1812        instance_id: int,
1813        plug: builders.PlugSocketBuilder | collections.Mapping[str, int],
1814        character_id: int,
1815        membership_type: enums.MembershipType | int,
1816    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
1817        """Insert a plug into a socketed item.
1818
1819        .. note::
1820            OAuth2: AdvancedWriteActions scope is required
1821
1822        Parameters
1823        ----------
1824        action_token : `str`
1825            Action token provided by the AwaGetActionToken API call.
1826        instance_id : `int`
1827            The item instance id that's plug inserted.
1828        plug : `aiobungie.builders.PlugSocketBuilder | Mapping[str, int]`
1829            Either a PlugSocketBuilder object or a raw dict contains key, value for the plug entries.
1830
1831        Example
1832        -------
1833        ```py
1834        plug = (
1835            aiobungie.PlugSocketBuilder()
1836            .set_socket_array(0)
1837            .set_socket_index(0)
1838            .set_plug_item(3023847)
1839            .collect()
1840        )
1841        await insert_socket_plug_free(..., plug=plug)
1842        ```
1843        character_id : `int`
1844            The character's id.
1845        membership_type : `aiobungie.aiobungie.MembershipType | int`
1846            The membership type.
1847
1848        Returns
1849        -------
1850        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
1851            A JSON object contains the changed item details.
1852
1853        Raises
1854        ------
1855        `aiobungie.Unauthorized`
1856            The access token was wrong or no access token passed.
1857        """
1858

2139    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:

2144

2148            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
2149        type : `typing.Literal[0, 1]`
2150            Type of the advanced write action. Its either 0 or 1.
2151            If set to 0 that means it `None`. Otherwise if 1 that means its insert plugs.

2154

2161            The Destiny character ID to perform this action on.
2162
2163        Returns
2164        -------
2165        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
2166            A JSON object response.
2167        """

2302    @abc.abstractmethod
2303    async def fetch_application_api_usage(
2304        self,
2305        access_token: str,
2306        application_id: int,
2307        /,
2308        *,
2309        start: datetime.datetime | None = None,
2310        end: datetime.datetime | None = None,
2311    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
2312        """Fetch a Bungie application's API usage.
2313
2314        Parameters
2315        ----------
2316        access_token : `str`
2317            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
2318        application_id : `int`
2319            The application id to get.
2320
2321        Other Parameters
2322        ----------------
2323        start : `datetime.datetime | None`
2324            A datetime object can be used to collect the start of the application usage.
2325            This is limited and can go back to 30 days maximum.
2326
2327            If this is left to `None`. It will return the last 24 hours.
2328        end : `datetime.datetime | None`
2329            A datetime object can be used to collect the end of the application usage.
2330
2331            If this is left to `None`. It will return `now`.
2332
2333        Example
2334        -------
2335        ```py
2336        import datetime
2337
2338        # Fetch data from 2021 Dec 10th to 2021 Dec 20th
2339        await fetch_application_api_usage(
2340            start=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 10),
2341            end=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 20)
2342        )
2343        ```
2344
2345        Returns
2346        -------
2347        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
2348            A JSON object of the application usage details.
2349        """
2350

115        self,

121    ) -> pathlib.Path:

123
124        Example
125        -------
126        ```py
127        manifest = await rest.download_json_manifest()
128        with open(manifest, "r") as f:

130            item_definitions = to_dict['DestinyInventoryItemDefinition']
131        ```
132
133        Parameters
134        ----------

139        language: `str`

143

145        -------
146        `pathlib.Path`
147            The path of this JSON manifest.
148        """

Download the Bungie manifest json file.

Example
manifest = await rest.download_json_manifest()
with open(manifest, "r") as f:
    to_dict = json.loads(f.read())
    item_definitions = to_dict['DestinyInventoryItemDefinition']
Parameters
  • file_name (str): The file name to save the manifest json file. Default is manifest.
  • path (str | pathlib.Path): The path to save the manifest json file. Default is the current directory. Example "D:/"
  • language (str): The manifest database language bytes to get. Default is English.
  • executor (concurrent.futures.Executor | None): An optional executor which will be used to write the bytes of the manifest.

  • pathlib.Path: The path of this JSON manifest.
@abc.abstractmethod
async def download_sqlite_manifest( self, language: Literal['en', 'fr', 'es', 'es-mx', 'de', 'it', 'ja', 'pt-br', 'ru', 'pl', 'ko', 'zh-cht', 'zh-chs'] = 'en', name: str = 'manifest', path: str | pathlib.Path = '.', *, force: bool = False, executor: concurrent.futures._base.Executor | None = None) -> pathlib.Path: 
150    @abc.abstractmethod
151    async def download_sqlite_manifest(
152        self,
153        language: _ALLOWED_LANGS = "en",
154        name: str = "manifest",
155        path: str | pathlib.Path = ".",
156        *,
157        force: bool = False,
158        executor: concurrent.futures.Executor | None = None,
159    ) -> pathlib.Path:
160        """Downloads the SQLite version of Destiny2's Manifest.
161
162        Example
163        -------
164        ```py
165        manifest = await rest.download_sqlite_manifest()
166        with sqlite3.connect(manifest) as conn:
167            ...
168        ```
169
170        Parameters
171        ----------
172        language : `str`
173            The manifest language to download, Default is English.
174        path: `str` | `pathlib.Path`
175            The path to download this manifest. Example `"/tmp/databases/"`, Default is the current directory.
176        name : `str`
177            The manifest database file name. Default is `manifest`
178        force : `bool`
179            Whether to force the download. Default is `False`. However if set to true the old
180            file will get unlinked and a new one will begin to download.
181        executor: `concurrent.futures.Executor | None`
182            An optional executor which will be used to write the bytes of the manifest.
183
184        Returns
185        --------
186        `pathlib.Path`
187            A pathlib object of the `.sqlite` file.
188
189        Raises
190        ------
191        `FileExistsError`
192            If the manifest file exists and `force` is `False`.
193        `ValueError`
194            If the provided language was not recognized.
195        """

Downloads the SQLite version of Destiny2's Manifest.

Example
manifest = await rest.download_sqlite_manifest()
with sqlite3.connect(manifest) as conn:
    ...
Parameters
  • language (str): The manifest language to download, Default is English.
  • path (str | pathlib.Path): The path to download this manifest. Example "/tmp/databases/", Default is the current directory.
  • name (str): The manifest database file name. Default is manifest
  • force (bool): Whether to force the download. Default is False. However if set to true the old file will get unlinked and a new one will begin to download.
  • executor (concurrent.futures.Executor | None): An optional executor which will be used to write the bytes of the manifest.
Returns
  • pathlib.Path: A pathlib object of the .sqlite file.
Raises
  • FileExistsError: If the manifest file exists and force is False.
  • ValueError: If the provided language was not recognized.

2302    @abc.abstractmethod

2307        /,

2309        start: datetime.datetime | None = None,
2310        end: datetime.datetime | None = None,
2311    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
2312        """Fetch a Bungie application's API usage.
2313
2314        Parameters
2315        ----------
2316        access_token : `str`
2317            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
2318        application_id : `int`
2319            The application id to get.
2320
2321        Other Parameters
2322        ----------------
2323        start : `datetime.datetime | None`
2324            A datetime object can be used to collect the start of the application usage.
2325            This is limited and can go back to 30 days maximum.
2326
2327            If this is left to `None`. It will return the last 24 hours.
2328        end : `datetime.datetime | None`
2329            A datetime object can be used to collect the end of the application usage.
2330
2331            If this is left to `None`. It will return `now`.
2332
2333        Example
2334        -------
2335        ```py
2336        import datetime
2337
2338        # Fetch data from 2021 Dec 10th to 2021 Dec 20th
2339        await fetch_application_api_usage(
2340            start=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 10),
2341            end=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 20)
2342        )
2343        ```
2344
2345        Returns
2346        -------
2347        `aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject`
2348            A JSON object of the application usage details.
2349        """

Fetch a Bungie application's API usage.

Parameters
  • access_token (str): The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
  • application_id (int): The application id to get.
Other Parameters

  • start (datetime.datetime | None): A datetime object can be used to collect the start of the application usage. This is limited and can go back to 30 days maximum.

    If this is left to None. It will return the last 24 hours.

  • end (datetime.datetime | None): A datetime object can be used to collect the end of the application usage.

    If this is left to None. It will return now.

Example
import datetime

# Fetch data from 2021 Dec 10th to 2021 Dec 20th
await fetch_application_api_usage(
    start=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 10),
    end=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 20)
)
Returns
  • aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject: A JSON object of the application usage details.
